akari is +16h away [HolyTrinity] 26-Feb-21 01:52 AM
@vivi alrgiht i looked over ur fox ch1 overall gud work, but there are some things i want u to go bk and fix so that u dont develop bad habits for future chpters
first of all, be very careful when ur redrawing relatively straight lines to align them. these ones are rather simple with plain bg and super thin sfx so u have tons of source material to use to clone or copy
if u align ur cloning or whatver it'll not be so wobbly
there r many instances of wobbly lines when there r a lot of avaible material to copy
n this is a more srs one since its a panel border and u hv it wobbly too
and the other circle is cuz thing on his chest is a bow the guy abv has it displayed clearer (edited)
another major thing u nid be careful abt is panel borders i noticed this on ur test that they get tampered with when u CTRL+T stuff and u dont notice or fix them in the end
this sfx the stuff under the panel is not white
(and wobbly lines again
the sfx hardly covers the line bt u overdrew
and made it such that it became disjointed (edited)
this sfx also (i alrdy forgot.. page 2?) (edited)
its not white near the edges (edited)
best use an adjustment layer to check if u cant see with ur monitor
this one at the bottom of p6 is pretty major (edited)
cuz theres a black line that marks the start of a panel on page 7 but u drew over it with a white brush
it'll be more obvious when the page is stitched together
wobbly lines + random overdrawing
woBBLE
1
if there are too many spdlines to clone without dying there r lots of ways to recreate
3 fast way r like
clicking once with mouse on the fat end and tapping gently once with tablet pen at the tip (1) (edited)
or vellona's method in #scanlation-tutorial https://discord.com/channels/558280453824446474/732788837230706689/732810338533113927 (2) (edited)
if u dont have pen pressure u can also change the brush setting to fade (3) (edited)
(pic of the 3 results) (edited)
the number 500 is distance in pixels it takes to taper off (webtoon is like 680px wide to give u perspective) (edited)
